  <content>
    <learning>
      <learningContent>
        <title>Brake System Inspection</title>
        <lcInstruction>
          <description>
            <figure>
              <title></title>
              <graphic infoEntityIdent="ICN-S1000DBIKE-AAA-DA00000-A-06RT9-00094-A-001-01" />
            </figure>
            <levelledPara id="para-000">
              <levelledPara id="para-001">
                <para>
							  To keep your brake system running like it should, it's a good idea to periodically give it a thorough inspection.
						  </para>
                <para>
							  Check the brake levers; they should be tight. When applied, they should work smoothly, and there should be a 1-inch clearance from the handlebar.
						  </para>
                <figure>
                  <title></title>
                  <graphic infoEntityIdent="ICN-S1000DBIKE-AAA-DA10000-A-06RT9-00133-A-001-01" />
                </figure>
              </levelledPara>
              <levelledPara id="para-002">
                <para>The brake cables should be taut and free of damage. There should be no breaks or frayed ends. Open the brake lever, and check for fraying near the anchor ball at the end of the cable.</para>
                <figure>
                  <title></title>
                  <graphic infoEntityIdent="ICN-S1000DBIKE-AAA-DA10000-A-06RT9-00134-A-001-01" />
                </figure>
              </levelledPara>
              <levelledPara id="para-003">
                <para>Look closely at the brake pads. Ensure that they are not worn and are hitting the wheels evenly. There should be at least 3/16-inch of rubber on the brake shoes.</para>
                <figure>
                  <title></title>
                  <graphic infoEntityIdent="ICN-S1000DBIKE-AAA-DA10000-A-06RT9-00135-A-001-01" />
                </figure>
              </levelledPara>
              <levelledPara id="para-004">
                <para>
							  Check all of the assembly's hardware, such as nuts and bolts, to ensure none is missing and each is held securely in place.
						  </para>
                <figure>
                  <title></title>
                  <graphic infoEntityIdent="ICN-S1000DBIKE-AAA-DA10000-A-06RT9-00136-A-001-01" />
                </figure>
              </levelledPara>
            </levelledPara>
            <para>
              <emphasis>Use the arrows to view the slide show.</emphasis>
            </para>
          </description>
        </lcInstruction>
      </learningContent>
    </learning>
